class Solution {
    public boolean canSortArray(int[] nums) {
        int lastCnt = 0;
        int lastGroupMax = 0;
        int curGroupMax = 0;
        for (int num : nums) {
            int curCnt = Integer.bitCount(num);
            if (curCnt == lastCnt) {
                curGroupMax = Math.max(curGroupMax, num);
            } else {
                lastCnt = curCnt;
                lastGroupMax = curGroupMax;
                curGroupMax = num;
            }
            if (num < lastGroupMax) {
                return false;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }
}

Explanation:
The method Integer.bitCount(num) is used to count the number of set bits in a given integer num. The for-each loop iterates over each number in the input array nums. 
If the current number has the same number of set bits as the previous number, curGroupMax is updated to be the maximum of the current number and curGroupMax. 
If the current number has a different number of set bits, lastCnt and lastGroupMax are updated to the current number and curGroupMax, and curGroupMax is reset to be the current number. 
If any number in the array is less than lastGroupMax, the array cannot be sorted using the given operation, so false is returned. Otherwise, the array can be sorted, so true is returned.

